				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Zemi's guide to swarm kiting<a name="74148"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 8 05 1:36 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Just a few things which may be helpful.
<br />

<br />
1) Do 5 LDoN's in BB and get yourself a Gravestone of Dire Melodies for 220 points. This is a Type 3 Aug which acts as a Wind Instrument. No more swapping.
<br />

<br />
If you have Epic, you're all set. If you have Epic, I hope you don;t need this guide hehe.
<br />

<br />
2) Buy a d*mn good drum with the best modifer possible. Thuderous Drums of Karana or Muramite War Drum are reasonable.
<br />

<br />
3) Set up a toggle target key. I personally use my number pad for all my songs and use the number pad ENTER key for toggle target. This will be useful for cc as well.
<br />

<br />
The reason for the toggle target key is all the aggro your pet generated by beating on your chosen target will now be owned by YOU. You want the next target to become your new pet once you finished your chant.
<br />

<br />
Also with your pet's target being the next pet in your lineup, you can lay down some chants on it to speed things up. 
<br />

<br />
Remember the key here is how fast can you get your pet's health down within chant range. 
<br />

<br />
4) Songs I loaded are 1) Selo's Accelerating Chorus, 2-5) Chants, 6) Largos Absonant Binding, 7) Bellow AA,<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-11.gif" border="0" alt="Cool" hspace="2" />Fufil's DoT (Have 9 song slots, ignore if you don;t) 9) Charm and 0) Invis song.
<br />

<br />
Just some thoughts. 
<br />

<br />
Initially, when I have 10-15 in my swarm, I start invis at 40-50%. This usually lands my pets health in the teens. 
<br />

<br />
When you get down to 3-4 in your swarm, let them hit your pet down to 20% before singing invis.
<br />

<br />
When you have two left, use the toggle and help your pet by chanting. Break invis when your chant target hits 25% then toggle chant both down. Example: if your pet is at 40% health and the former target is at 20%, use 3-chants on former pet and 1 or 2 on the other and toggle back and forth. After practice you can have them die within seconds of each other. 
<br />

<br />
I have found that I can kill the entire Nightstalker camp in PoN before the first corpse rots. Depending on Lag. This will reward you with some nice exp and time to loot.
<br />

<br />
If you find another bard in your favorite Kiting area, kindly ask them to send a tell when they are getting ready to log. Being polite will get you everywhere. 
<br />

<br />
If someone trains you while swarming, don't forget to thank them when you're done for the extra experience. 
<br />

